q1: It's a game where two players have a choice and a third one is a passive observer. If the two players choose to report the true value, all players receive similar pay. But if they choose a different value they can earn more money at the expense of the third players pay. If player 1 decides to increase the value reported, player 2 can decide to find out if player 1 was truthful or not and then decide to reverse their choice, go along with it or change it to something else. Whatever his choice, both player 1 and 2 receive the same amount and player 3 either receives the same or less than them.
The goal of this study was to determine how a group of people would report a number based on the amount of earnings they would receive.
To try and make the most amount of money fairly
